# Pipeline Equalization — {{PROJECT}}

A pipeline change never touches just 1 layer — it touches the coherent set. Skipping a layer = silent bug.

> Template — adapt the layers to the project's real architecture. Examples below for common stacks.

## The N layers

### For Next.js + DB

```
C1  TYPES / SCHEMAS     src/types/, src/schemas/
C2  DB MIGRATIONS       drizzle/migrations/, supabase/migrations/
C3  REPOSITORIES        src/repositories/ (DB access)
C4  SERVICES            src/services/ (business logic)
C5  SERVER ACTIONS      src/app/.../actions.ts
C6  API ROUTES          src/app/api/.../route.ts
C7  HOOKS               src/hooks/ (client)
C8  COMPONENTS          src/components/
C9  PAGES               src/app/.../page.tsx
C10 GLOBAL STATE        src/stores/, contexts
C11 EXT INTEGRATIONS    third-party APIs
```

### For LLM agent + tools

```
C1  PERSONA / PROMPT     prompts/, persona/
C2  TOOLS SPEC           tools/spec.ts (JSON schemas)
C3  TOOL HANDLERS        tools/handlers.ts
C4  AGENT LOOP           agent.ts (orchestrator)
C5  WEBHOOK / ENTRY      api/webhook/
C6  DB STATE             conversation tables, context
C7  INTEGRATIONS         LLM provider, voice, messaging
```

### For CLI / backend service

```
C1  TYPES / DOMAIN       src/types/
C2  DB / STORAGE         src/storage/
C3  SERVICES             src/services/
C4  COMMANDS / HANDLERS  src/commands/
C5  HTTP / IPC LAYER     src/http/, src/ipc/
C6  CONFIG / ENV         config/
C7  INTEGRATIONS         external APIs
```

## Required sequences by change type

### Add a new entity
1. Types/schemas (C1)
2. Migration (C2)
3. Repository/storage (C3)
4. Service (C4)
5. API/handler (C5/C6)
6. UI (C7-C9)
7. E2E smoke test

### Change a critical flow
1. Map all touched layers BEFORE coding
2. Each layer has an isolated test
3. Smoke test the full flow

## Anti-pattern: partial merge

❌ "I only touched the API, forgot to update the UI" → contract breaks in production
❌ "I changed the type, forgot to migrate the DB" → hydration error

**Before opening a PR:** mental checklist "did I touch C1-CN where needed? did I verify coherence?".

## Where to catalog a large change

Every change that reaches **3+ layers** becomes `docs/casos-referencia/YYYY-MM-DD-titulo.md` documenting touched layers and decisions.
